1. As owner of the White Sox from 1900 until his death in 1931, Comiskey oversaw building Comiskey Park in 1910 and winning five American League pennants (1900, 1901, 1906, 1917, 1919) and two World Series (1906, 1917).;
2. He was a key person in the formation of the American League, and was also founding owner of the Chicago White Sox.;
